Former Wits University Vice-Chancellor is receiving backlash for using the N-word during a virtual meeting with SOAS University of London students. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Wits University Vice-Chancellor is receiving backlash for using the N-word during a virtual meeting with students in the UK. Habib can be heard in a clip circulating on social media saying he comes from a part of the world where the use of the word is acceptable. Students at the SOAS University of London were left dismayed by Habib's utterances. READ: Adam Habib resigns from Wits University He is the director of the institution. Students were unimpressed with Habib's attempts to explain himself. Habib said, "I'm sorry I offended you. I come from a part of the world where when somebody uses it, the context matters."